snippet.textDisplay: It's not the interviewers' fault, these are questions they were given from people higher up, she's just doing her job. I've seen someone say before that bighit has a list of questions that the interviewers can pick from and it's not that long, I don't know if it's true, but that would explain the repetitive questions. I also think she might've been a little nervous, but it still wasn't as bad as Ryan Secrest snatching the mic away from Namjoon before they could finish introducing themselves, talking over Namjoon and cutting him off, asking whether the rest of bts ever get annoyed with the answers Namjoon gives (to which Yoongi responded clearly annoyed because what kind of question is that?) At least this woman had sense enough not to stand in front of Taehyung the entire time, blocking him like Ryan Secrest, and held the mic out the entire time just in case the other members wanted to say something because they do sometimes.
